text: McPherson County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, 399 people lived there. The county seat is Tryon. It was named after James B. McPherson. The county was founded in 1890 from parts of Logan County. ==History== It was founded in 1890. The county gained its current boundaries in 1913 when land was given to Arthur County. ==References== Category:19th- century establishments in Nebraska Category:1890 establishments in the United States Category:Nebraska counties
title: McPherson County, Nebraska
